item.content:encoded: I can guarentee for you that it doesn't return appetite (now), with TACOS and pizzas, or TACOS and Cipher. Got a TACO activation on my first TACO of the day from Cipher, no app gained. Got a TACOS activation at the same time as a Pizza no app activation- no app gained. Yes, they can both proc- whether that's a bug or not I don't know- but they won't somehow break the code and give you a refund of appetite. Most likely it just sets the value of the appetite reduction to 0, in order to prevent exactly that breaking. Quite possibly it was that way before, when BlackRuby did it, but has since been changed to prevent that sort of exploit.
